Response ID: resp_158
Response Text: I am very concerned that a small group of arts representatives have dominated access to the new ACME leadership, with the rest of the community learning only recently that those individuals have been lobbying ACME for changes to how arts funding is distributed. I was deeply concerned to see that 50% matching funds for COA funding is back on the table. This sort of matching fund is a huge barrier to groups that don’t have wealthy donors to cover their funding gaps, and specifically discourages FREE events by effectively requiring arts to charge in order to match. How can we serve our low income communities if we need to charge them ticket prices we can’t afford ourselves? This kind of mindset is intrinsically keeps the arts in the hands of a privileged minority.

